cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper describes a fully automated translation system based on predefined phrases and rules, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The system also employs machine learning techniques to improve the quality of translations, which could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses user surveys and the assessment of language quality, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
